From ed085c04918dd53e11219cecfde7d9706a5a95be Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thomas Grainger <tagrain@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 10:37:25 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] tcp: reset the connection on a valid RST at rcv_nxt under a
 delayed ACK

RFC 5961 3.2 requires a RST with SEG.SEQ == RCV.NXT to reset the connection.
tcp_do_segment() tests the exact-match reset condition against last_ack_sent
instead of rcv_nxt, and anchors the acceptance window's right edge on
last_ack_sent + rcv_wnd. When the receiver has delayed-ACKed data
(rcv_nxt > last_ack_sent), a valid RST at rcv_nxt (the peer's SND.NXT) is
either answered with a challenge ACK instead of resetting, or -- once rcv_wnd
has shrunk below the delayed-ACK gap -- dropped by the window check before the
reset test is reached. Either way the connection is left ESTABLISHED
(half-open): the peer that sent the RST has already fully closed, so nothing
retransmits it.

Accept a RST at rcv_nxt as an exact match in the reset test, and anchor the
window's right edge on rcv_nxt + rcv_wnd. This matches the behaviour OpenBSD
(tcp_input.c rev 1.194, 2005) and NetBSD (rev 1.296, 2009) adopted for the
same delayed-ACK RST failure.

---
 sys/netinet/tcp_input.c | 5 +++--
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sys/netinet/tcp_input.c b/sys/netinet/tcp_input.c
index 35a9d76..74c58f4 100644
--- a/sys/netinet/tcp_input.c
+++ b/sys/netinet/tcp_input.c
@@ -2129,14 +2129,15 @@ tcp_do_segment(struct tcpcb *tp, struct mbuf *m, struct tcphdr *th,
 		 *   covered by the RFC.
 		 */
 		if ((SEQ_GEQ(th->th_seq, tp->last_ack_sent) &&
-		    SEQ_LT(th->th_seq, tp->last_ack_sent + tp->rcv_wnd)) ||
+		    SEQ_LT(th->th_seq, tp->rcv_nxt + tp->rcv_wnd)) ||
 		    (tp->rcv_wnd == 0 && tp->last_ack_sent == th->th_seq)) {
 			KASSERT(tp->t_state != TCPS_SYN_SENT,
 			    ("%s: TH_RST for TCPS_SYN_SENT th %p tp %p",
 			    __func__, th, tp));
 
 			if (V_tcp_insecure_rst ||
-			    tp->last_ack_sent == th->th_seq) {
+			    tp->last_ack_sent == th->th_seq ||
+			    tp->rcv_nxt == th->th_seq) {
 				TCPSTAT_INC(tcps_drops);
 				/* Drop the connection. */
 				switch (tp->t_state) {
